  "eprint": {
    "title": "A post-quantum key exchange protocol from the intersection of quadric surfaces",
    "authors": [
      {
        "name": "Daniele Di Tullio",
        "email": "danieleditullio@hotmail",
        "affiliation": ""
      },
      {
        "name": "Manoj Gyawali",
        "email": "gyawali@ncit",
        "affiliation": ""
      }
    ],
    "abstract": "In this paper, we present a key exchange protocol in which Alice\nand Bob have secret keys given by quadric surfaces embedded in a\nlarge ambient space by means of the Veronese embedding and\npublic keys given by hyperplanes containing the embedded quadrics.\nBoth of them reconstruct the isomorphism class of the intersection\nwhich is a curve of genus 1, which is uniquely determined by the\nj-invariant. An eavesdropper, to find this j-invariant, has to solve\nproblems which are conjecturally quantum resistant.",
    "keywords": [
      "Quadric surfaces",
      "Veronese embedding",
      "Segre embedding",
      "Post-quantum cryptography"
    ],
    "category": "Cryptographic protocols",
    "publication_info": "Preprint. MINOR revision.",
    "last_updated": "2020-06-03",
